{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "6296046d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "1. Is the Python Standard Library included with PyInputPlus?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "7ac8ff49",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "PyInputPlus is a Python module used for taking inputs with additional validation features. \n",
    "PyInputPlus will keep asking the user for text until they enter valid input."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "9f119aa8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "2. Why is PyInputPlus commonly imported with import pyinputplus as pypi?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b73ae0de",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "You can import the module with import pyinputplus as pyip\n",
    "so that you can enter a shorter name when calling the module's functions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "a1ddfa52",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "3. How do you distinguish between inputInt() and inputFloat()?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "5b06a96b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "nputInt() : Accepts an integer value. \n",
    "This also takes additional parameters ‘min’, ‘max’, ‘greaterThan’ and ‘lessThan’  for bounds. Returns an int.\n",
    "inputFloat() : Accepts a floating-point numeric value. \n",
    "Also takes additional ‘min’, ‘max’, ‘greaterThan’ and ‘lessThan’  parameters. Returns a float."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "f90d8ef0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "4. Using PyInputPlus, how do you ensure that the user enters a whole number between 0 and 99?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "dcf34798",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "inp = pyip.inputInt(prompt = \"Enter an Integer... \",\n",
    "                    min = 0, lessThan = 100)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "af24f3a3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "5. What is transferred to the keyword arguments allowRegexes and blockRegexes?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "df661702",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "e can allow blank values as valid input by setting the blank parameter as True.  Certain inputs can be blocked (that is, these values are invalidated) by setting the blockRegexes \n",
    "parameter’s value as the regex pattern we want to invalidate."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "bd80e849",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "6. If a blank input is entered three times, what does inputStr(limit=3) do?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "d63dee01",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The limit parameter is used to specify the maximum number of tries the user has for entering a valid input, after which the default value is returned, \n",
    "if specified, or a RetryLimitException is raised otherwise."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "111f6b92",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "7. If blank input is entered three times, what does inputStr(limit=3, default='hello') do?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "b8fe1218",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "if blank input entered more than three times then it takes hello as input"
   ]
  },
